trg_text: Cabinet is taking advice on the matter School Safety Summit Cabinet welcomes the recently held School Safety Summit hosted under the leadership of Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekg The summit brought together education and external stakeholders to find solutions to safety issues facing the country s schools as well as to pave the way forward for safer environments in school This follows incidents of violence at some schools, including the tragic death of the 24-year-old teacher, Mr Gadimang Daniel Mokolobate, who was fatally stabbed by a learner at the Ramotshere Secondary School in Zeerust, North Wes All stakeholders agreed that violence in general, and in schools in particular, is not acceptable and that further cooperation is required to ensure that schools become safer for both learners and teachers Matric exams Cabinet wishes all learners, especially Grade 12 learners, well over this perio For the first time, the department will this year also administer an examination in South African Sign Language at Home Language level to 58 deaf candidates across 10 school The examination extends over five-and-a-half weeks and will conclude on 28 Novembe Learners across the country will also sign a voluntary pledge to commit to upholding the integrity of the examinations by not participating in any malpractic Parents and guardians are encouraged to support learners during this critical period in their academic journe It is also vital to motivate learners to finish their schoolin Cabinet decisions9.

trg_text: Cabinet approved the publication of the Children s Amendment Bill in the Government Gazette for public comment The Bill seeks to strengthen coordination of the child-care and protection system through interdepartmental and intersectoral collaboratio The amendments respond to the North Gauteng High Court Judgement of November 2017, wherein the Department of Social Development was ordered to prepare and introduce the necessary amendments to the Children s Act, 2005 (Act 38 of 2005) in respect to the legal solution towards the management of the foster-care syste Cabinet approved the introduction of the Postal Services Amendment Bill to Parliamen The Bill gives effect to the National Integrated ICT Policy White Paper that was approved by Cabinet in September 2016.The intended outcomes are to have a competitive, viable and sustainable South African Post Office that provides/facilitates universal services and access as well as the transformation of the postal secto The Bill also provides an approach to assigning physical addresses to rural and traditional communitieThis Bill has already gone through public consultatio Upcoming events13.

src_text: Khonferense ya Afrika Borwa ya Dipeelet o t a Bodit habat habaMopresidente Ramaphosa o tlare ka Labohlano, 26 Diphalane 2018, a tsorama maemo a modulasetulo Khonferenseng ya pulamadibogo ya Afrika Borwa ya Dipeelet o kua Sandton Convention Centre go la Johannesbur Ye ke karolo mehutahuta ya matsapa a go goka dipeelet o le go godi a ikonom Se sengwe gape ke gore baemedi ba bane ba dipeelet o bao ba thwet wego ke Mopresidente ba tla begela khonferense ka mo omo wa bona go lebelet we kgatelopele yeo e fihlelet weg Samiti ya Dipeelet o ya Sehlopha sa Dinaga t e 20 (G20)Mopresidente Ramaphosa o memilwe ke Dikantorokgolo t a Selete sa Germany, Ngaka Angela Merkel, go kgatha tema Samiting ya Dipeelet o ya G20 ya Dikgwebo t a Gemany le Kopanokgwebong ya Dinaga t a Afrika (CwA), le Sehlophaphethi i sa Merero ya Kgwebo, t e ka bobedi ga t ona di tlo swarelwa kua Berlin, Germany ka la 30 Diphalane 2018.Samiti ya Dipeelet o ya G20 e tla kopant ha mmogo dikgwebo t a Germany le dinaga t a CwA go phuruphut a menyetla ya dipeelet o ka fase ga tlhako ya Kgwebi anommogo ya G20 le Afrik Babeelet i ba Germany ba tla laet a diprot eke t a maemo a godimo t eo gabjale di dirwago dinageng t a CwA le go phuruphut a menyetla ye mengwe mo kontinenten Mopresidente o tla ba gona samiting bjalo ka modulasetulo wa bobedi wa Sehlopha sa Boelet i sa Afrika sa G20.

src_text: Kabinete e lebogi a Tona ya Maphelo, Ngaka Aaron Motsoaledi, yo a amogedit wego difoka t e pedi t a go hlomphega t a Kochon, kua moletlong wa difoka t e bego di swerwe kua Hague, Netherland Sefoka sa pele ke sa maikarabelo a Tona ka boyena a le no i ka baka la maitapi o a gagwe le boetapele bja sepolotiki mo twant hong ya bolwet i bja mafahla (TB) lefaseng ka bopharSefoka sa bobedi seo Tona a tla se abelanago le Leloko la go Hlomphega Nick Hebert, Moleloko wa Palamente (MP) gola United Kingdom e tlaba mabokgoni a bona bjalo ka baduladitulo ba mohlakanelwa ba Kopano ya Maloko a Palamente Lefaseng ka Bophara ka TB ba go t wa dinageng ka moka lefasen Sefoka sa Kochon se fiwa ngwaga ka ngwaga go batho le/goba mekgatlo yeo e kgathilego tema ye bohlokwa go lwant ha TB e kaba ba le dinageng t a bona goba lefaseng ka bophar Kabinete e amogela Difoka t a 2018 t a Lefase t a Boeti fao Afrika Borwa e kgethilwego bjalo ka Naga ye Etelet ego dinaga pele mo Afrik Durban, KwaZulu-Natal le yona e hlaot we bjalo ka Toropokgolo ye Etelet ego Ditoropo t a Afrika pele le go ithopela leina la mabonwa la Boemakepe bjo t wago pele mo Afrika bja Maeto ka dikep Motsekapa, gola Kapa Bodikela e ikhweledit e leina la Lefelo le t wago pele mo Afrika la Ditiragalo le Meketek Kabinete e amogela tiragat o sefaleng sa filimo ye dirilwego ka mo nageng ya go bit wa Nommer 37 ye hlagi it wego ke modiradifilimo Joshua Bradley wa kua Amerika ka la 2 Dibatsela 2018.

src_text: Filimo ya bohlagahlaga ka seemo sa bosenyi ye theilwego ka ditiragalo t a Cape Flats e thekgilwe ke Kgoro ya Bogwebi le Intasteri ka dit helete ka sekimo sa yona sa Afrika Borwa sa Diputselet o t a Badiradifilimo ba Bafsa ba Bathobas Se se tla thu a go goka dipeelet o t a thwi t a dinageng t a ka ntle gore di beelet e ka gare ga intasteri ya Afrika Borwa ya difilimMahloko19.
